Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Assistant Manager, Customer Service (FT Exempt) St Catharines , ON Description Posted: Wednesday, April 19, 2023 Closes: Sunday, April 30, 2023, 5:00 pm Assistant Manager, Customer Service (Full-Time) Exempt Location: Central Library Job Summary: This position reports to the Manager, Customer Service and is accountable for coordinating the customer service experience related to public services such as circulation and information services across the Library system. This position will lead the Branch Librarians and staff to provide pro-active, accessible and responsible Library service consistently across the Library system. This position will supervise, coach and develop staff and volunteers including preparation of schedules and performance management. As part of the Management Team will plan and develop strategies to meet community needs and position St. Catharines Public Library as a leader in Library service in the Niagara Region. Supervisory Relationships: Branch Librarians, Under the direction of the Manager Customer Service, leads the Customer Service Team to ensure a pro-active, accessible and responsible customer centric experience and removal of barriers for customers, Collaborates with the Management Team. Duties and Responsibilities: Library Services Ensures the Library’s policies and procedures provide a customer centric experience and eliminates any unnecessary barriers for customers: Provides leadership for all customer service functions across the system; Under the direction of the Manager Customer Service, leads the Customer Service Team in development and implementation of pro-active, accessible and responsive customer-centered, efficient and consistent services, policies and procedures involving customer interactions; Looks for and evaluates the effectiveness and efficiency of all activities related to Customer Services provided to the community.Investigates and evaluates new customer services and implementation details, including efficiencies in current processes and practices. Works closely with the Manager of Programming &amp; Promotions, to ensure Customer Service staff support programs and outreach in the community. Training May assist in the development, implementation and coordination of training and onboarding of new staff for the system. Will identify other training needs for staff. Community Develops and maintains good working relationships in the community, by building partnerships with other organizations to further the Library’s mission and overall goals.Advocates and promotes the value of the Library and its programs in the community and to outside agencies with professionalism.Participates in the hiring, evaluation, scheduling, investigating, disciplining, and motivating of staff who directly report to this position, and other staff as it relates to assigned teams.Conducts performance evaluations and ongoing coaching of staff to support and develop staff while achieving the Library’s goals.Recommends and provides input to the Management Team regarding development of policies, procedures and strategies for Library services, including efficiencies in workflow, staffing levels, processes/procedures in accordance with current Library trends, analysis of Library statistics and innovative new technologies;Works collaboratively with other members of the Management Team and staff in decision making, planning, goal setting and public relations for the Library as a whole;Suggests and implements staff training on relevant topics for programs, promotion and outreach services and other topics;Takes responsibility to maintain a broad, in-depth awareness and knowledge of the Library’s role in the community and the community’s needs of the Library, in order to better inform the rest of the Library’s Management Team;Provides input for collection development as requested;Assumes responsibility to act on behalf of another member of the Management Team as required.Master’s Degree in Library Science from an ALA accredited Library school.Minimum 3 years of progressive and relevant managerial or supervisory experience.Demonstrated leadership and supervisory experience in a collaborative work environment. Leadership &amp; Coaching Management As part of the Management Team, leads and supports the effective operations of the Library. This involves: Working Conditions: Fosters and maintains positive work relationships with Library staff; Contributes to healthy and safe work environment while supporting the Library’s mission and values; This is a system-wide position that will be working at all location of St Catharines Public Library; Hours of work will include evenings and weekends to support the work of the Library; May participate as the management representative on committees, such as the Joint Health and Safety Committee and the Labour Management Committee; Driver’s licence required for travel between branches and/or in the community; Works in compliance with any legislation, including the Occupational Health and Safety Act, the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act, and municipal, provincial and federal privacy legislation. Qualifications: Experience: Hours of Work: Weekdays, evenings, and weekends as required, 35 hours per week. Salary: $72,812.00 - $85,180.00 per year (Pay Group 5, Base, 2022 Terms of Employment, Exempt Employees). How to Apply: Please submit your cover letter and current resume to hr@myscpl.ca . We thank all who apply. Only those selected for an interview will be contacted. St. Catharines Public Library is an equal opportunity employer committed to inclusive, barrier-free recruitment, selection processes, and work environments.COVID-19 vaccines are a requirement of the job unless you have an exemption on a medical or other protected ground pursuant to the Ontario Human Rights Code (OHRC). Please advise Human Resources to ensure your accommodation needs under the OHRC and Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act are provided through all stages of the recruitment process. Compensation $72,812.00 - $85,180.00 per year Closes: 30 April, 2023 St. Catharines Public Library St Catharines , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
