Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? 2023-06 Library Technician (RPT) North Vancouver , BC Description The North Vancouver City Library is seeking an enthusiastic, adaptable and technologically savvy Library Technician with a passion for service to young people to join our team part-time (22 hours per week).As part of the Youth and Family Services team, this position participates in a range of library public services for all ages and audiences, including information and reader’s advisory service, programming and outreach, and collection management activities. A commitment to customer service rooted in equity and respect is essential.This position has a strong focus on services to children, teens, families and caregivers. The successful candidate will be able to demonstrate: Knowledge of developmental milestones and the ability to prepare and deliver age-appropriate programming and outreach for early years, school-aged children and teens and their families and caregivers Knowledge of key resources and literatures, and the ability to provide age-appropriate reference and reader’s advisory services in the Children’s department and The Room, a space dedicated to teens Creative ideas and a commitment to ongoing learning in the field Familiarity with STEAM (Science Technology Engineering Arts and Mathematics) concepts and practices Strong technology and instructional skillsIf you are passionate about providing exceptional customer service and creative programming, and if you enjoy being part of a dynamic team, then we would love to hear from you!QualificationsYou will have completed a Library Technician diploma program including relevant courses, plus have some customer service and library experience, or an equivalent combination of relevant training and experience.Knowledge or experience in outreach, community development, or behavioural and developmental support for youth would be an asset.Apply to: Deb Hutchison Koep, Chief Librarian, https://www.nvcl.ca/about#jobsNote: When uploading documents to your profile, the maximum size allowed per document is 1MB.Please ensure the document file name and file extension is all lower case (i.e. .pdf and not .PDF). If you are having difficulty attaching documents, please click on the “question mark” icon on the top right side of the screen for technical support.Start date: May 17, 2023Schedule:Wednesday – 1 – 5 p.m.Thursday – 9:30 a.m. – 5 p.m.Friday – 9:30 a.m. – 5 p.m.Saturday – 1 – 5 p.m.Schedules are reviewed periodically and subject to change. Evening and weekend work is required.Closing date: May 1, 2023 at 5 p.m. PDTNorth Vancouver City Library is committed to recruiting and hiring candidates that reflect thecommunity we serve. We welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds, including Indigenouscandidates, all identities, candidates who speak languages in addition to English, and personswith disabilities. Accommodations are available on request for candidates in all parts of the selection process. Compensation $27.43 – $32.23/hour (pay grade 16; 2021 rates), plus 10% in lieu of benefits Closes: 1 May, 2023 North Vancouver City Library North Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
