Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Assistant Branch Supervisor - Bookmobile Walkerton Description We are looking for 2 Part-Time Assistant Branch Supervisors to join our Library Services team supporting the Bookmobile! Bruce County "Bold and beautiful Bruce County ... a healthy, caring community of prosperity and innovation." The journey to an ever better Bruce County will be marked by exploration, inquiry and discovery. A place powered by innovation and shared values. A place where we help people who live, and work here make great personal choices and also reflect the public interest. Because of this mind-set, we do some pretty amazing things! Join our team powered by innovation and shared values where explorers turn obstacles into opportunities and individual challenges into shared solutions. Come join us on roads less travelled and turn your journey into an adventure. www.brucecounty.on.ca Bruce County Public Library Bruce County Public Library is a vibrant hub and pillar of the community and believes in a future where innovative ideas fundamentally change the way our communities learn, play, explore and connect with each other. Our mission is to provide the information, knowledge, and entertainment resources you need to achieve your goals, foster your interests, and realize your dreams. From e-books to fishing rods, STEAM activities to educational workshops, Bruce County Public Library offers something for everyone. With 17 physical branches and a variety of online resources, Bruce County Public Library can be accessed worldwide for free with a library card. With over 22,000 card holders, the public library circulates over 428,000 items per year. The Library plays a fundamental role in lifelong learning by promoting innovation, providing an outlet for creative pursuits, and balancing new and exciting technologies with existing services. Bookmobile Literacy, remote communities, senior isolation and mobility, and financial barriers to library and internet access can all be tackled through a mobile library service serving Bruce County. Services to smaller and remote communities continue to be a significant need, and the idea for a bookmobile was born. The Bruce County Public library has secured and modified a vehicle, the ‘bookmobile’ that will deliver scheduled visits and programs across the county. By visiting strategic locations and events, users will have a meeting place that enables them to develop relationships, build on common interests, and enhance their literacy and lives. Register for a library card, check out and return materials, participate in programming, or borrow tech – the Bookmobile will reach hundreds of people across the County providing accessibility to library services for everyone! Learn more about us: https://library.brucecounty.on.ca Location Lakeshore Hub – Port Elgin, Ontario This position will travel throughout Bruce County providing library services from the BCPL Bookmobile. Salary The wage range for this position is $31.98 to $37.62 per hour. Schedule Position One Week 1: Monday 9:00am - 2:30pm Tuesday 8:30am - 3:30pm Week 2: Wednesday 8:30am - 4:00pm Thursday 8:30am - 4:30pm Friday 8:30am - 4:00pm Position Two Week 1: Wednesday 8:30am - 4:00pm Thursday 8:30am - 4:30pm Friday 8:30am - 4:00pm Week 2: Monday 9:00am - 2:30pm Tuesday 8:30am - 3:30pm Hours are subject to change. Additional hours may be required for special events including stat holidays, evenings, and weekends. Benefits Percentage paid in lieu of benefits and vacation Opportunity to enroll in the OMERS Pension PlanAccess to an Employee Assistance ProgramEmployee Referral Bonus Program (Long Term Care)Educational Assistance for skills development and career advancementEmployee Discounts to enjoy great savings on entertainment, travel, shopping, health &amp; wellness, sport and more! Health, Safety &amp; Wellness Health &amp; Safety ProgramWorkplace Mental Health ProgramHealth &amp; Wellness Committee ActivitiesWinter Loan Program offering equipment rentals for you discover Bruce County’s winter wonderland! About the job Reporting to the Assistant Director, the Assistant Branch Supervisor - Bookmobile, drives the Bookmobile (extended-length transit van) across Bruce County to attend scheduled stops and community events. The incumbent ensures a welcoming library environment and ensures the smooth operation of the Mobile Library through exceptional customer service, circulation functions, provision of Bookmobile programming as well as direct implementation of programs and community outreach. The position involves a great deal of multitasking, organizational skills, and the ability to make decisions quickly and decisively. The incumbent undertakes supervisory duties for any volunteers, clerks, summer students or pages assisting with the Bookmobile. Requirements Two-year post-secondary diploma in Library Sciences or a related fieldOne year of previous experience in a unionized library, including providing programming for all agesAdvanced computer skillsProficiency in Microsoft Office programsExcellent writing skills, including proper spelling, grammar, and punctuationAbility to identify issues and implement creative and strategic solutions to overcome problemsAbility to plan, organize, develop, implement, and interpret goals, objectives, and policiesValid Class G Driver’s LicenseCurrent First Aid/CPR certification is considered an assetAble to lift up to 30 pounds (will need to load materials in bins)Able to stand for extended periods (may have to stand for duration of a stop (~60 minutes) Interested applicants should review the entire job posting at www.brucecounty.on.ca, and then apply online, following the outlined process. The deadline for applications is April 30, 2023, at midnight. Diversity &amp; Inclusion The Corporation of the County of Bruce is an equal opportunity employer committed to an inclusive, barrier-free recruitment and selection process. If contacted for an employment opportunity, please advise Human Resources if you require accommodation. Privacy Personal information contained in applications will be used for recruitment purposes and collected as per the Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act, R.S.O. 1990, Chapter M.56. REQ: 2023-072 Compensation The wage range for this position is $31.98 to $37.62 per hour. Closes: 30 April, 2023 County of Bruce Walkerton Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
