Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Collections Librarian Limited Term Appointment (ending April 30, 2025) Antigonish , NS Description The Angus L. Macdonald Library, St. Francis Xavier University, invites applications from qualified candidates for a limited term librarian position at the rank of Librarian I. This is a leave replacement, with an end date of April 30, 2025. The Angus L. Macdonald Library serves one of Canada's top-ranked undergraduate educational institutions and sees its role as a proactive one of service and support for the academic success of its students and faculty. Position Description: Reporting to the University Librarian, the successful applicant participates in library services, including regularly scheduled reference desk and Live Help shifts; and serves as Liaison Librarian to designated departments and/or programs, providing specialized information literacy instruction, research assistance, and support for library resource selection and evaluation to those departments. This position will have functional responsibility for collections activities, which include acquisitions, cataloguing, and collection management of both physical and electronic resources. Other duties include, but are not limited to, outreach to students and faculty, participation in library initiatives and projects, and the creation and maintenance of subject research guides. A detailed position description can be viewed here. Compensation $65,561 - $70,750 Closes: 23 April, 2023 Angus L. Macdonald Library - St. Francis Xavier University Antigonish , NS Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
