Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Director of Library Services CORNWALL , ON Description The United Counties of Stormont, Dundas and Glengarry (SDG) is located along the St. Lawrence River in the south-eastern corner of Ontario. SDG is “Where Ontario Began”, and is rich in heritage, tradition, and culture with an abundance of historical sites, great events, and beautiful attractions. With a population of 65,000, SDG is primarily rural yet close to urban centres such as Cornwall, Ottawa, and Brockville.The Stormont, Dundas and Glengarry County Library is presently accepting applications for the full-time senior management position of Director of Library Services. The Director of Library Services is responsible to the Stormont, Dundas and Glengarry County Library Board, and fulfills the duties and responsibilities of Chief Executive Officer in accordance with the Public Libraries Act. Administratively, the SDG Library Board is integrated with the municipality and functions as the County Library Services Department. Main duties include but are not limited to: Responsible and accountable for the efficient and effective operation of the Library Services Department.Work collaboratively with the SDG Library Board and the County’s Chief Administrative Officer to formulate policies and procedures for the Library Services Department in compliance with all legislated requirements of the Public Libraries Act.Establish Departmental goals and objectives for approval by the SDG Library Board. On an annual basis, evaluate the operation of the Department and report on the achievement of approved goals and objectives.Maintain continuing liaison with the SDG Library Board, the Chief Administrative Officer and the County Executive Management Team, other library systems and associations, government departments, the general public and the media to actively promote library services and positive public relations.Ensure the sound financial management of the Library Services Department via the preparation and monitoring of the Department’s annual budget, liaison with the Director of Financial Services/Treasurer and Chief Administrative Officer, and reporting to the SDG Library Board and County Council as required. Apply for additional funding when available through grant programs etc., ensuring all funding requirements are met. Ensure compliance with all County and SDG Library Board policies and procedures relating to financial matters, including, but not limited to, purchasing, use of equipment/vehicles, asset preservation, etc.Develop appropriate Library IT needs and services in coordination with overall county IT goals and objectives.Participate as a member of the Counties Executive Management Team in the development and administration of County policies and procedures and ensure uniformity in their implementation.In consultation with the CAO, responsible for the management and administration of all department staff, which includes the hiring, orientation, scheduling, disciplining and performance evaluations in accordance with the County Personnel Policy Manual.Foster good rapport and cooperative business relationships; develop and maintain a contact network with professionals in the field and counterparts in other municipalities; investigate the feasibility of shared services and programs with neighbouring municipalities. Political acumen with tact and discretion in handling matters of a confidential or politically sensitive nature. Attendance at meetings of the SDG Library Board and County Council to report on Library Services activities and to respond to questions. Participate in programs, attend conferences and courses which foster professional or technical development where applicable and approved.Ensures that Library operations are in compliance with all applicable health and safety legislation and County Health &amp; Safety policies/procedures. Responsible for reporting and correcting non-compliance or possible safety risks. Qualifications: Possession of a Master’s degree in Library Science and or a degree in Business Administration, or an equivalent combination of education and experience.A minimum of 5 to 8 years of progressively responsible senior management experience, preferably in a municipal or public library setting with proven communication skills.Must have superior public relations, time management, organizational and analytical skills.A comprehensive understanding of federal, provincial and municipal legislation is desirable.Ability to provide a current satisfactory Criminal Record Check.In accordance with SDG County’s Vaccination Verification Policy Coronavirus (COVID-19), all new hires will be required, as a condition of employment, to provide proof of COVID-19 full vaccination status as defined by the Ontario Ministry of Health.2023 Salary Range:$115,009 to $134,544 with full benefit package and pensionLocation: County Administrative Office, 26 Pitt Street, Cornwall, ONInterested and qualified candidates are invited to visit our website at www.sdgcounties.ca to obtain the complete instruction package on how to apply. Applications will be received until 12:00 noon on Friday, April 21, 2023. We thank all applicants for their interest, however, only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Personal information received in this application will be used solely for employee selection purposes and will be handled in accordance with the Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act. We will accommodate the needs of applicants under the Human Rights Code during the hiring process. Compensation $115,009 to $134,544 with full benefit package and pension Closes: 21 April, 2023 The Stormont, Dundas and Glengarry County Library CORNWALL , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
