Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? LIAISON LIBRARIAN, MARKETING (PART-TIME) Toronto , ON Description Seneca Libraries, Toronto, ON, CanadaLocation: Seneca@York Campus, with liaison duties at Newnham and SIA campuses as requiredSchedule: 1 day minimum on campus per week, work hours are flexible and determined by operational need Position Type: Faculty (Academic), Part-Time, 24 hours per week Start Date: ASAPCompensation: The range for part-time librarians is from $43.95 to $76.25 per hour (6% vacation pay included). Upon hire, the incumbent will receive a pay calculation to determine their step within the range. We are proud to be building the equitable Seneca, and welcome applications from candidates who can contribute to the diversity of lived experiences, perspectives and approaches. Joining Seneca means being part of an inclusive community working hard to dismantle barriers to access, student success and employee potential. If you require accommodation during any part of the recruitment process, please contact joanne.hoffmann@senecacollege.ca. Position Summary: This position reports to the Manager, Library Literacies, Instruction, and Outreach and works collaboratively with the librarians and staff on the Literacies team. This librarian must have a highly developed interest in the application of information and teaching technologies in post-secondary education, specifically in teaching advanced market research skills. This librarian will have knowledge of and concern for the learning needs of students, strong interest in flexible teaching and learning theories, ability to work with faculty and staff in a collaborative environment, and a commitment to innovation. This librarian will provide information literacy pedagogy for market research in FCAD in collaboration with colleagues at all campuses. The librarian supports the academic integrity policies of the college and offers expertise in building skills for the ethical and legal use of information. This professional position provides liaison and collaboration with teaching faculty in various programs across campuses. The librarian works closely with faculty members across the college as colleagues and peers. The librarian brings to the position specific theoretical and applied knowledge of subject collections, information organization and the integration of information literacy competencies in academia as a lifelong skill. Responsibilities: Under the direction of the library manager, the part-time librarian will: Teach information literacy competencies to learners through various modalities to support assigned Schools and programs.Keep teaching materials and planning up-to-date, current and relevant using the documentation system (available through the team intranet).Keep tutorials, library packages and videos up to date, reviewing content at least once a semester or based on changes to databases, ILS, college strategic and academic plans, School or program changes.Author, develop and contribute to several subject guides under assigned Schools and programs.Conduct regular virtual research appointments.Deliver training to faculty on Leganto as required; promoting and communicating library resources and services; and working collaboratively as part of a team to build assessment tools.Actively communicate to library staff related IL teaching activities and support, including notifying user services staff of any research/library assignments and related solutions or strategies; demonstrating online IL tutorials and activities used in teaching.Collaboratively guide Information Literacy technician(s) to provide pedagogical structure and direction of information literacy content for first semester courses in non-degree programs.Support digital literacies instruction as required or assigned.Be familiar with the robust hybrid collection of electronic &amp; print books, article databases, journals and other resources that support FCAD Faculty, Schools and Program needs and the college’s strategic missionDevelop and maintain an in-depth awareness of program/School/Faculty needs through the review of program curriculum, subject outlines and assignments.Judiciously promote licensed resources, open educational resources, and materials available under fair dealing to the FCAD communityWork collaboratively with colleagues and management for cross-team library training events, and in the exchange of ideas to improve communication and collaboration activities.Serve on relevant library and/or college committees and represent the library at external meetings or conferencesCommunicate goals, library policies, guidelines, resources and services to faculty, staff, and studentsPerforms other duties as requiredQualifications:Education:Master’s Degree in library science or information science from an ALA-accredited institution or equivalent degree Experience:3-4 years of professional library experience with progressive responsibilities in an academic library, including information literacy instruction.Demonstrated experience in the use of products and tools such as LibGuides by Springshare, Leganto, and Primo by ExLibris and familiarity with BlackBoardStrong interest in market researchStrong analytical, problem solving and organizational skills Demonstrated initiative, flexibility, and ability to work creatively and effectively in both collaborative and independent settings Strong understanding of key issues and trends in the design and delivery of library instruction in support of the academic mission of Seneca and experience creating and delivering learning outcomes.Excellent communication and interpersonal skills including the ability to explain complex concepts to a wide range of users in individual and group settingsSensitivity to and understanding of the diverse academic, socioeconomic, cultural, disability and ethnic backgrounds of community college students and staffPreferred:Familiarly with educational strategies for a more virtual learning environment, including educational technology tools and instruction platformsFamiliarity with market research information resources Familiarity with the rules of MLA and APA citation and ethical use of information is an asset; Ability to multi-task and prioritize to meet deadlines and ability to manage a diverse workloadEvidence of continued professional development, involvement and contributionTo apply: Email joanne.hoffmann@senecacollege.ca your resume and cover letter, with the email subject header “PT Marketing Liaison Librarian”. If you are contacted for an interview, please note that a skills assessment will be required during the recruitment process. NOTE: Seneca requires copies of educational credentials at the time of an interview. Confirmation of educational credentials in the form of an official Canadian transcript or an official evaluation of international credentials which determines Canadian equivalency will be required upon offer of position. We thank all applicants for their interest in this position, however, only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation The range for part-time librarians is from $43.95 to $76.25 per hour (6% vacation pay included). Upon hire, the incumbent will receive a pay calculation to determine their step within the range. Closes: 21 April, 2023 Seneca Libraries Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
