Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Bibliothécaire responsable du développement des compétences informationnelles - Poste à terme d’un an Winnipeg , MB Description The University of Saint-BonifaceFounded in 1818, Université de Saint-Boniface is the first and only French-language university in Manitoba and Western Canada. It has to its credit 26 college and university programs distributed among ten faculties, schools and departments, and welcomes 1,400 students as well as 2,000 people in continuing education.USB is located in Old Saint-Boniface, a historic French-speaking neighborhood in the very heart of the city of Winnipeg. The Alfred-Monnin LibraryThe Alfred-Monnin Library offers services and documentary resources in French supporting research, teaching and learning at the Université de Saint-Boniface. Job description The librarian is responsible for creating/adapting, offering and promoting a program that promotes the acquisition and development of information skills in students. The incumbent reports to the Library management and is part of the research assistance service team. Responsibilities:Transmits information skills to students, face-to-face and virtually, in groups or individually (in the classroom or in the workshop as well as by video capsules);Facilitates the integration of information literacy into courses and assignments by collaborating with academic units and faculty members;Plans and organizes strategic activities promoting the development and understanding of information literacy among students and faculty members;Stay abreast of standards and new trends in information literacy;As a member of the research assistance team, advises users on the choice of relevant databases, citation methods, informs them of recognized practices, recommends the best strategies in documentary research, and trains them in tools specialized search engine (eg Library Search Tool);Participates in the maintenance and development of the Library's website, thematic guides on LibGuides and other virtual tools;Collaborates with other members of the Library team to plan and deliver a variety of activities (promotional or otherwise) on campus.Qualifications sought:Master's degree in library or information science from a program accredited by the American Library Association or its equivalent and preferably one year of relevant experience;Undergraduate university degree in social and human sciences or sciences or in an appropriate field of specialization;Previous experience in a university library (desired);Excellent written and oral communication skills in French and English;Knowledge of computerized library systems and research tools, new technologies and emerging protocols as well as mastery of office software and databases;Demonstrated ability to work independently or collaboratively, to take on a multitude of administrative or professional responsibilities simultaneously, and to know how to manage priorities and time;Ability to communicate in a variety of styles and for different audiences, e.g. ex. oral presentations, writing reports with text or data, effective use of social media, blogs, forums and email;Good interpersonal communication demonstrating diplomacy, flexibility, collaboration, good ability to analyze and solve challenges;Demonstrated ability to initiate, implement and manage an activity.Start date: August 1, 2023 (one-year term position) Remuneration: according to the collective agreement (Professional II) Please apply by uploading your cover letter and resume no later than Friday, April 28, 2023 at ustboniface.ca/jobs . All information received will be treated confidentially and only successful candidates will be contacted. Applications submitted by email will not be accepted. For more information, do not hesitate to contact the human resources department at srh@ustboniface.ca. USB is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion in employment. We strongly encourage people who identify as female or non-binary, Indigenous, with disabilities, and visible minorities to apply. USB is committed to providing a welcoming and barrier-free experience for people with accessibility needs. It is possible to request accommodation measures at any stage of the recruitment process. To make a request in complete confidentiality, send an email directly to the Human Resources Department srh@ustboniface.ca so that the necessary arrangements can be made. Compensation Selon la convention collective - Professionnel II (min. 63 034,71 $) Closes: 28 April, 2023 Bibliothèque Alfred-Monnin, Université de Saint-Boniface Winnipeg , MB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
